1
00:00:01,244 --> 00:00:03,953
To err is human.

2
00:00:04,801 --> 00:00:10,861
To err is inevitable for all
being not perfect.

3
00:00:11,041 --> 00:00:16,598
Still no one wants to remain
imperfect.

4
00:00:16,891 --> 00:00:20,645
There is an element within all
that is animate

5
00:00:21,062 --> 00:00:24,071
that tends towards perfection.

6
00:00:24,821 --> 00:00:26,475
If it were not so,

7
00:00:26,475 --> 00:00:28,765
we would feel
no want at all.

8
00:00:29,891 --> 00:00:31,952
Our tendency 
towards perfection

9
00:00:32,541 --> 00:00:34,957
is certainly very weak
and limited.

10
00:00:36,138 --> 00:00:39,388
Otherwise we could attain
the goal at once.

11
00:00:40,928 --> 00:00:45,653
Our limited capacity and tendency
for perfection

12
00:00:46,073 --> 00:00:47,673
makes room for the guide

13
00:00:48,223 --> 00:00:49,697
or guru.

14
00:00:51,292 --> 00:00:53,904
The imperfect is not so

15
00:00:53,962 --> 00:00:56,364
if it is not in need of help

16
00:00:56,628 --> 00:00:59,127
and that also
from beyond itself.

17
00:01:01,027 --> 00:01:02,837
The perfect is not perfect

18
00:01:03,751 --> 00:01:06,103
if he cannot assert Himself

19
00:01:06,103 --> 00:01:07,398
or help others

20
00:01:07,858 --> 00:01:10,398
and that too of His own accord.

21
00:01:12,028 --> 00:01:14,680
So the guidance to perfection

22
00:01:14,993 --> 00:01:16,226
or Absolute Truth

23
00:01:17,026 --> 00:01:18,670
is necessarily a function

24
00:01:19,100 --> 00:01:21,150
of the absolute Himself
 

25
00:01:22,830 --> 00:01:24,489
and the divine agent

26
00:01:24,849 --> 00:01:26,879
through
whom this function manifests

27
00:01:26,949 --> 00:01:28,696
is Sri Guru

28
00:01:29,456 --> 00:01:32,052
 
or the Divine Guide.

